               <floruit notBefore="1607" notAfter="1632">He was a dignitary in the court of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe </roleName> 
                  <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos">Susǝnyos</persName>, who enjoyed many political and military titles. In <date>1609</date>,
                  he was appointed as a governor of <placeName ref="LOC6144Wagara">Wagarā</placeName>. 
                  A year later, he became an army chief, <roleName type="title">ʾarʾsta ḥārā</roleName>. And again in September <date>1614</date>,
                  he became <roleName type="title">liqa ḍabāʾit</roleName>. In <date>1621</date>, he was appointed as <roleName type="title">ʾAbagāz</roleName>.
